
[1]affirmative

   AFFIRM'ATIVE, a.

   1. That affirms, or asserts; declaratory of what exists; opposed to
   negative; as, an affirmative proposition.

   2. Confirmative; ratifying; as, an act affirmative of common law.

   3. In algebra, positive; a term applied to numbers which have the sign
   + plus, denoting addition, and opposed to negative, or such as have the
   sign - minus, denoting subtraction.

   4. Positive; dogmatic. Obs.

    AFFIRM'ATIVE, n. That side of a question which affirms or maintains;
    opposed to negative; as, there were seventy votes in the affirmative,
                      and thirty-five in the negative.
